title: What could we do with the domain name?
body: Let's discuss to see if there are any plans to add a web application in the future. We currently have the domain `harmoney.space` until Jan 17, 2021.

title: Look into improving the structure of back-end code by adding in more middleware
body:

title: Investigate network error bug with requests to an http server
body:
iOS and Android seem to block requests to an HTTP server by default. Thus our React-Native front-end cannot send any requests to the back-end. There is a setting that can be disabled that allows you to access an HTTP server. However, we are currently using Expo as the development environment, rather than Xcode/Android Studio Code. To my knowledge, I'm not sure if we can disable this setting using Expo.

Alternatively, investigate using [ngrok](https://ngrok.com/). 

Also look into CORS for the front-end?

title: Add Stripe to handle payments
body:
As a User, I want to be able to create an account with a balance

Docs are here: https://stripe.com/docs/api

"You can use the Stripe API in test mode, which does not affect your live data or interact with the banking networks. The API key you use to authenticate the request determines whether the request is live mode or test mode."

Seems like we can use test mode to keep mock account balances
